during his collegiate studies and his reading for the law , he wrote little poetry , but encounters with the graveyard poets and then wordsworth regenerated his passion for " the witchery of song . "   poetry " thanatopsis " is bryant 's most famous poem , which bryant may have been working on as early as 1811 .

poets & poetry : william cullen bryant was just 17 when he wrote this poem whose name comes from the greek for " view of death "

" thanatopsis "